cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.AR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the design of a PHY/MAC layer for IoT traffic in 5G networks. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper proposes a CDMA based transmission scheme for low power IoT devices. 
- cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) is relevant as the paper discusses the inefficiencies of existing LTE protocols in handling IoT traffic and proposes a solution for it. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the proposed system involves the use of Software Defined Radios (SDRs) for the PHY/MAC layer. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the implementation of the proposed system.
